{
  "root_causes": [
    {
      "type": "Speed/Duplex negotiation mismatch",
      "cause": "R1 is configured for auto-negotiation while the remote peer (R2) is configured with a forced 100Mbps / half-duplex; this mismatch commonly produces receive/input errors.",
      "evidence": [
        "R1 running-config: GigabitEthernet0/0/1 Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:negotiation: { \"auto\": true }",
        "R2 running-config: GigabitEthernet0/0/1 Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:speed: { \"value-100\": [...] }, Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:duplex: \"half\", Cisco-IOS-XE-ethernet:negotiation: { \"auto\": false }",
        "R1 interface counters: GigabitEthernet0/0/1 input_errors = 70 (get_interface_status)",
        "R1 and R2 IPs on GigabitEthernet0/0/1 are 10.0.0.1/30 and 10.0.0.2/30 respectively (running-config) — indicates they are the peer endpoints"
      ],
      "confidence": 0.95
